It turns out `SwingWorker` posts instances of `Runnable` to the `EventQueue` using a `javax.swing.Timer` with exactly that `DELAY`.

    private static class DoSubmitAccumulativeRunnable 
          extends AccumulativeRunnable&lt;Runnable&gt; implements ActionListener {
        private final static int DELAY = (int) (1000 / 30);
        ...
    }

You can get a higher frame rate, but not with `javax.swing.SwingWorker`. You can build `SwingWorker` from [source][1], but eventually you saturate the thread with instances of `Runnable`. One alternative is to run the model flat out and sample it periodically, as shown [here][2].


