Tomcat 10.0 and 10.1 are **not** full Jakarta EE 9.1 application servers: you shouldn&#39;t use the `jakarta.jakartaee-web-api` artifact, which would imply that the runtime supports all Jakarta EE 9.1 [*Web Profile*][1] technologies. 

Tomcat does not implement all the specs required in *Web Profile*. At least four other products do. See [this list][2] for Jakarta Web Profile 9.1: 

 - Apache TomEE
 - Eclipse Glassfish
 - IBM Open Liberty
 - Red Hat WildFly

You can find the list of supported technologies on [Tomcat&#39;s web site](https://tomcat.apache.org/whichversion.html) and for Tomcat 10 they translate to this list shown as a [Maven POM][3] snippet.

```lang-xml
    &lt;dependency&gt;
      &lt;groupId&gt;jakarta.servlet&lt;/groupId&gt;
      &lt;artifactId&gt;jakarta.servlet-api&lt;/artifactId&gt;
